## Summary of what drove the brief

**Event load: HEAVY** — gated by **NVDA Q1 FY2027 earnings after the close**, the day's defining catalyst.

Three competing storylines structured the report:
- **AI-semis melt-up** — MU +7.9% ($1T market cap), TSM +4.0% and MRVL +5.9% (reports BMO) on NVIDIA's $150B spending news; Goldman lifted its S&P target to 8,000.
- **Cybersecurity rout** — ZS **−24.7%** (earnings collapse, broke below all moving averages) dragging an overbought platform cohort: PANW −4.1% (RSI 79), CRWD −3.7% (RSI 87), FTNT −3.3% (RSI 88), S −5.1%, OKTA −4.0%.
- **Space squeeze** — MNTS +48%, RDW +14%, LUNR +12.8%, PL +8.5%, RKLB +7.5% on the SpaceX $2.29B Space Force win + IPO hype.

Macro backdrop: futures green and tech-led, VIX 16.87 (normal, no pre-NVDA fear premium), WTI −3.3% on Iran-deal optimism, crypto weak (BTC clinging to $75K).

## Rule compliance
- **No fabricated data** — all six calendar events (NVDA, Logan, ADP, Richmond, Cook, API) marked **Pending** since every Actual was "—". MRVL/NVDA earnings shown with no results.
- **Every number sourced** with attribution (Schwab/CoinGecko/Stooq/FRED/Opus feed).
